fields.name: Cool Planet Labs
fields.org_mission: Hometowns is a community created, community curated, community controlled social connection platform.  Think user-controlled Facebook with deeper place-based integration, promoting local sharing economy and local connection.  Self-sustaining monetization will be controlled from the bottom up (e.g., crowdsourced selection of who can advertise/sponsor), not the top down. Content and privacy will be determined by the users, not by corporate dictate.  Hometowns has a value proposition, a team assembled and relationships with large existing networks including Sierra Club, Transition Towns, etc.  Hometowns' next step is to prototype the technology platform for show and tell with investors and to release to alpha user communities for feedback and iteration.

fields.name: Alliance for Change
fields.org_mission: The mission of the Alliance for CHANGE is to facilitate the healthy and safe reintegration of incarcerated men and women back into society.  We recognize that this requires an active process of re-socialization, including pre-parole and post-parole community support.  Our program incorporates core principles of social justice and community living as well as practical skills that ensure successful reintegration and lifestyle change that is beneficial to the participant as well as his or her larger community.

The Learning Shelter will provide a 90 day education program that teaches Machines skills in 3D printing, laser cutting, welding combined with soft skills training that expose participants to new technologies and opportunities for jobs.

fields.name: homefrontfan
fields.short_desc: Connecting female veterans with resources to help them find jobs and community.
fields.description:
Inspired by the Department of Labor's Female Veterans Data Challenge for National Day of Civic Hacking 2013, we are taking on female veterans unemployment, because despite available resources, veterans are unemployed, and our female veterans are the worst off, with 30% higher unemployment. 

We launch projects to introduce new experiences to real users, our veterans, and gain insights to uncover the solution. For our first project, homefrontfan campaigns, we partnered with Crowdtilt, the Bay Area startup with the easiest way to groupfund anything, and Reallocate, the Bay Area organization that connects social good projects with collaborators. Heroes have an opportunity to go outside their network and meet homefrontfan supporters through campaigns that groupfund aspects of their job search.

fields.name: Husika Kenya!
fields.short_desc: Inform and empower Kenyan citizens with access to information about public administration and service delivery.
fields.description: In March 2013 the Kenyan government began the process of devolving from a highly centralized structure that included eight provinces and 408 districts to a structure with two levels of government: national and county. Devolution and the formation of 47 semi-autonomous counties is viewed as a way to increase democratic processes and reduce corruption. Existing sources of information about public administration and service delivery focus entirely on the national level. While there are national level sources of information in Kenya, there are not similar sources of information that focus on the new counties, themselves. Picture the difficulties you would have, with very limited access to information about public administration and local service delivery in the place where you live!
